51.9	City_of_Halifax	Halifax (former city)	The City of Halifax was an incorporated city in Nova Scotia, Canada. On April 1, 1996, the government of Nova Scotia dissolved the City of Halifax, and amalgamated the four municipalities within Halifax County and formed Halifax Regional Municipality, a single-tier regional government covering that whole area. (There are no longer any cities in Nova Scotia.) The city was the capital of Nova Scotia and shire town of Halifax County. It was also the largest city in Atlantic Canada.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c1/Halifaxnighttime.jpg/250px-Halifaxnighttime.jpg
